Service Types in Kubernetes
==========================

1. ClusterIP
============
> default
> Internal access within the cluster
> No external access
>>commands:-
kubectl apply -f clusterip-service.yaml
kubectl get svc
kubectl run curlpod --image=radial/busyboxplus:curl -i --tty
# Inside a pod
curl clusterip-service

2. NodePort
===========
> Exposes the service on a static port(30000-32767) on each node.
> Accessible externally via <NodeIP>:<NodePort>
>>commands:-
kubectl apply -f nodeport-service.yaml
kubectl get svc
minikube service nodeport-service --url
curl $(minikube service nodeport-service --url)

3. LoadBalancer
===============
> Exposes service externally using a cloud provider's load balancer.
> Automatically assigns an external IP
>>commands:-
kubectl apply -f loadbalancer-service.yaml
kubectl get svc loadbalancer-service
minikube tunnel  # if using Minikube
curl http://<EXTERNAL-IP>

